<P>
BEGINNING IN THE YEAR 2006 AN AVERAGE RESIDENTIAL USER SHOULD EXPECT TO PAY ABOUT 63-DOLLARS.
<P>
THAT'S ABOUT A 36-DOLLAR JUMP FROM THIS YEAR'S BILLS.
<P>
A CAL-AM SPOKESMAN SAYS COST DEPRECIATION SHOULD EVENTUALLY BRING THE BILLS BACK DOWN.
